race.comment: MALDINI (7) won a jumpout and resumed with a narrow defeat at Seymour 38 days ago. He's been gelded since and is further improved. He's sure to keep improving for the smart yard and this is winnable. MONT SAINT MICHEL (8) won this grade easily at Bairnsdale, quickly back on track. Carries more weight but has the inside gate and should go close. SOCIAL CONSCIENCE (2) also hits this at peak fitness and is going well enough to feature. Newitt sticks and he's back in grade. BEDTIME ANGEL (12) resumes. Broke her maiden last campaign which returned mixed results through four starts. Two trials in readiness for this have been encouraging.
